    en: "New York issues a non-driver photo ID through the Department of Motor Vehicles for residents who do not have a driver license. The card is valid government photo ID for voting, banking, employment, hospital admission, public benefits, air travel (Real ID and Enhanced versions), and any other purpose where a driver license is normally accepted. Anyone age 10 or older who is a NY resident can get one. Cost is reduced for people age 62 and older and waived for SSI recipients."
